<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-06-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="495" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Terres</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-06-28"><hi rend="italic">June 28,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1823.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith the
                            passport of Mr. Jose R. Paradis, who, on being informed of the decision
                            of the Department relative to his claim, handed same to our consular
                            agent, and which he has forwarded to this legation.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John B. Terres.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>